description: Beginning at Kenrokuen, one of the three most famous landscape gardens in Japan, we make our way down the Sai River towards the coast. Upon reaching the coast, we are able to follow a shared cycleway for 30 kilometres parallel to the ocean. At this point we cross the mouth of the Mae River, then follow the river until we reach the small town of Imaemachi for lunch. From there we continue following the river until we reach Lake Kiba. The lake is surrounded by a public park with a cycleway we can follow until reaching the main road. We follow the main road west until we reach Natadera temple. After a brief exploration we make one last push to Kaga, climbing one last hill to arrive in the main valley.
